==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[blostm|blōstm]], [[blostma|blōstma]]'', probably related to ''[[bloom]]''.  Cognate with Dutch ''[[bloesem]]''.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈblɒsəm/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#A [[flower]], especially indicative of fruit as seen on a fruit [[tree]] etc.; taken collectively as the mass of such flowers.
#:''The '''blossom''' has come early this year.''
#The state or season of producing such flowers.
#:''The orchard is in '''blossom'''.''

